WEBVTT

01:19.666 --> 01:23.040
- Evening, Mr Nobbs
- Miss Dawes

01:32.625 --> 01:35.624
- Good evening, Albert
- Mrs Baker, ma'am

01:35.708 --> 01:40.207
All right, girls  No finger-marks
on the knife blades, please

01:53.333 --> 01:54.957
Well,

01:55.041 --> 01:58.374
- Helen Dawes, what are you grinning
about? - Nothing, Mrs Baker

01:58.458 --> 02:00.832
Sorry, Mrs Baker

02:18.416 --> 02:22.540
Good evening, Mr and Mrs Moore
Your table awaits

02:29.250 --> 02:32.707
What sweet roses, Nobbs
You always remember

02:32.791 --> 02:34.874
Milady

02:40.875 --> 02:44.582
- Milady
- Good evening, Mrs Baker

02:45.333 --> 02:49.915
- Such a kind little man  - Who?
- Nobbs

02:50.000 --> 02:51.874
Oh, right

02:55.458 --> 02:57.082
What do you say,
the lamb or the beef?

02:57.166 --> 03:00.082
Will we be able to tell
the difference?

03:09.000 --> 03:10.832
Doctor Holloran

03:10.916 --> 03:12.999
Follow me

03:14.458 --> 03:18.749
- There now
- Thank you

03:18.833 --> 03:21.790
Have the lamb, Doctor Holloran
It will melt in your mouth

03:21.875 --> 03:24.332
The lamb it shall be, Duchess

03:24.708 --> 03:28.165
- Sean, Doctor Holloran
will take the lamb  - Yes, ma'am

03:30.166 --> 03:32.290
- Will you have the soup?
- l won't, thank you

03:32.375 --> 03:34.457
Sean

03:37.041 --> 03:40.124
- There's a stain on your tie
- Ma'am

03:40.208 --> 03:43.999
Have a care, Sean  Last week it was
the jacket  Tonight the tie

03:44.083 --> 03:46.124
- Yes, but
- Remember there are hundreds

03:46.208 --> 03:49.790
hundreds of young men walking the
streets of Dublin looking for work

03:49.875 --> 03:52.290
Young men, Sean

03:52.375 --> 03:54.457
Good man, Nobbs

03:58.083 --> 04:00.749
- Monsieur, madame
- Madame

04:01.541 --> 04:03.374
Madame, where is my glass
of iced water?

04:03.458 --> 04:05.957
Quick, Patrick

04:17.375 --> 04:19.957
- My Lordship
- Mrs Baker

04:22.708 --> 04:24.332
Terribly sorry

04:24.416 --> 04:27.249
I know we're late but could you
forgive us just this once?

04:27.333 --> 04:29.165
- We're simply famished
- Of course

04:29.250 --> 04:32.124
Aubrey insisted we walk
all the way from Ballsbridge

04:32.208 --> 04:35.832
There's nothing like a brisk walk
for giving the body an appetite

04:35.916 --> 04:39.124
Come along now,
your table is set and waiting

04:40.125 --> 04:42.707
Tell me, how is your mother,
dear Lady Yarrell?

04:42.791 --> 04:45.124
Tip-top, Mrs B  Tip-top

04:45.208 --> 04:47.040
I certainly hope
she'll come and visit us soon

04:47.125 --> 04:49.165
She'd be delighted, l'm sure

04:49.250 --> 04:53.624
- So sorry, dear lady  - No bother
at all, Mr Smythe-Willard

04:53.708 --> 04:55.707
to be sure

04:56.791 --> 05:00.332
My friends    we do apologise

05:02.625 --> 05:05.999
- Now, drinks
- Albert

05:28.833 --> 05:31.249
Bunny, you're a featherbrain

05:31.333 --> 05:34.499
No, he's not, he's brilliant!

05:34.583 --> 05:36.999
Do your Clara Westfield

05:37.458 --> 05:41.040
Dudley, call the brigade
My hair's on fire!

05:41.125 --> 05:42.749
My hair's on fire!

05:48.708 --> 05:51.457
A long old day, Mr Nobbs

05:55.333 --> 06:00.999
Well    l wouldn't say no to
a nightcap now, sure l wouldn't

06:02.583 --> 06:05.540
Only I haven't a drop left myself

06:07.416 --> 06:09.790
Goodnight, Mr Casey

06:12.583 --> 06:14.665
Mr Nobbs

06:31.958 --> 06:36.249
Half a crown from Mrs Moore
Six pence from the Doctor

06:36.333 --> 06:40.415
Tuppence    Monsieur Pigot

06:40.500 --> 06:43.624
Thruppence, Mrs Cavendish
when l brought her stationery

06:43.708 --> 06:48.082
Another thruppence from
what's-his-name, Viscount's friend

06:48.166 --> 06:51.540
Tanner from the Viscount
Another from his missus

06:56.458 --> 07:00.665
Two-and-six and six and two
is eight, three is eleven

07:00.750 --> 07:02.790
Three is one-and-two,
six is one-and-eight,

07:02.875 --> 07:06.040
six is two-and-two  That's

07:08.333 --> 07:11.207
4 shillings, 8 pence

08:11.625 --> 08:14.707
Mr Gilligan, madam, so good
to have had you with us again

08:14.791 --> 08:19.249
- l hope your stay was satisfactory?
- Yes, perfectly fine, thank you

08:27.000 --> 08:28.790
- Sorry, sir
- Look what you've done

08:28.875 --> 08:30.749
You've ruined my boots,
defaced my luggage

08:30.833 --> 08:32.415
I've never seen such blatant
incompetence

08:32.500 --> 08:36.207
- Are you all right, my dear?
- Does that look all right to you?

08:36.291 --> 08:39.290
- Where's that fool Sweeney?
- l'm very sorry, sir

08:39.375 --> 08:41.540
Yes, yes, everyone's sorry
It's outrageous ineptitude

08:42.333 --> 08:44.457
Clean up the mess
you've made of my boots

08:49.875 --> 08:54.582
I won't patronise this establishment
again and l will urge my friends

08:54.666 --> 08:57.749
and acquaintances to do the same
if you keep this man in your employ

08:57.833 --> 09:00.290
Yes, Mr Gilligan, sir

09:11.250 --> 09:13.457
- Dismiss him immediately
- Sir, I was to slip

09:13.541 --> 09:15.999
- Now!
- Yes, sir

09:16.916 --> 09:18.582
Fine

09:23.625 --> 09:25.832
Give us the marmalade there,
Mr Donaghue

09:33.375 --> 09:36.374
- lt's the marmalade
- The marmalade, Patrick

09:36.750 --> 09:40.082
Will you pass the marmalade
to Mr Casey?

09:40.166 --> 09:44.665
Always on Tuesdays,
if I recall correctly

09:44.750 --> 09:46.832
Thank you, Mr Nobbs

09:48.750 --> 09:52.082
- God, but isn't he a smasher?
- Who?

09:52.166 --> 09:55.457
- What's-his-name, the Viscount
- Not to mention rich

09:55.541 --> 09:58.624
Young and handsome
with money and land

09:58.708 --> 10:01.082
That's the kind of man l want

10:01.833 --> 10:04.874
I'll wear my new blouse tonight
and give him an eyeful

10:07.166 --> 10:10.874
Would you care for a tasty breast
of duck, my Lord?

10:10.958 --> 10:14.457
Pink and succulent
just the way you like it

10:17.375 --> 10:19.874
That's right, lower yourself

10:19.958 --> 10:22.540
The likes of him
would take advantage of a girl,

10:22.625 --> 10:23.999
then leave her high and dry

10:24.083 --> 10:26.957
High, maybe,
but I wouldn't say "dry"

10:27.041 --> 10:30.290
Girls, stop this tittle-tattling
and just get on with your breakfast

10:30.375 --> 10:34.249
It's no trouble at all, mind you

10:34.541 --> 10:36.999
- Morning, all
- Good morning

10:37.166 --> 10:42.124
Someone didn't bring me
my wake-up cuppa

10:43.750 --> 10:46.415
I'll have to lodge a complaint
with Mrs Baker

10:50.041 --> 10:52.749
- Morning, Nobbs
- Doctor

10:54.375 --> 10:58.749
- Did you know we have a Lord
and Lady staying? - ls that so?

10:59.666 --> 11:03.124
- What do you think? Any chance?
- l'm sorry, there's nothing here

11:03.208 --> 11:04.707
I was 2 years in The Ardlane

11:04.791 --> 11:07.749
- Maybe you should have stayed
there  - Well is there any

11:36.541 --> 11:38.540
- Good morning, Nobbs
- Hello, Nobbs

11:38.625 --> 11:41.874
Mistress Milly
Master George

12:18.750 --> 12:20.832
Bunny, breakfast

12:25.125 --> 12:26.790
Shall we wake the girls?

12:36.833 --> 12:39.707
Well, that hat's very important
Be careful with that

12:39.791 --> 12:43.082
Katie, get those sheets nice
and clean  Good girl

12:44.791 --> 12:50.915
- Are you the fellow about the
boiler for us? - l'm a boiler-man

12:51.000 --> 12:54.749
- You certainly took your sweet time
getting here  - Sorry, ma'am

12:54.833 --> 12:58.290
Mrs Baker's waiting inside
Come on inside, follow me

13:07.833 --> 13:12.249
- Mrs Baker  - Albert, Mr Hubert
Page is working in the morning,

13:12.333 --> 13:14.415
and he's come over
and asked us for a bed

13:14.500 --> 13:18.165
so l've told him he can muddle
in with you for one night

13:20.208 --> 13:22.582
With me, ma'am?

13:22.666 --> 13:25.249
Yes, Mr Nobbs, with you

13:25.333 --> 13:30.249
What?
What are you trying to say?

13:32.000 --> 13:35.499
- My bed is full of lumps
- Full of lumps?

13:37.291 --> 13:41.040
Your bed was re-picked
and buttoned just 6 months ago

13:41.125 --> 13:44.332
- What are you talking about?
- So it was, ma'am, so it was

13:44.416 --> 13:46.499
I'm a very light sleeper,

13:46.583 --> 13:48.540
and being sleepless might keep
Mr Page awake

13:48.625 --> 13:52.457
So I'm thinking he might be better
off on the sofa in the coffee room

13:52.541 --> 13:55.165
On the sofa? In the coffee room?

13:55.250 --> 13:57.957
I don't wish to be an inconvenience

13:58.041 --> 13:59.790
I'll keep myself warm
with a sharp walk

13:59.875 --> 14:03.124
You'll do nothing of the kind,
Mr Page

14:04.583 --> 14:06.790
Of course, Mrs Baker

14:06.875 --> 14:11.832
If Mr Page is pleased to share
my bed, he's welcome, l'm sure

14:11.916 --> 14:16.749
I should think so, indeed
Right, that's settled then

14:16.833 --> 14:21.332
Mrs Baker, ma'am  The man about
the boiler has just arrived

14:21.416 --> 14:23.915
Have you a letter from Holmans?

14:24.000 --> 14:26.415
Holmans? The plumbers?
No

14:26.500 --> 14:28.999
I thought you said
he was from Holmans?

14:29.083 --> 14:32.374
- Didn't they give you    - No,
I said nothing about Holmans

14:32.458 --> 14:35.374
- You said they gave you a letter
- l said I know about boilers

14:36.291 --> 14:39.124
And do you    know about boilers?

14:39.208 --> 14:44.165
I do, ma'am
I'm an apprentice boiler-man

14:45.083 --> 14:48.374
Well    since you're here,

14:48.458 --> 14:51.915
you might as well come and have
a look at the blessed thing

14:52.416 --> 14:55.915
- Thank you, Polly
- Thanks, ma'am

14:56.000 --> 14:57.790
Come on

15:03.708 --> 15:06.999
There now
It's the bane of our lives

15:07.083 --> 15:09.749
I'm depending on you to put
some manners on it

15:09.833 --> 15:12.207
We've our costume ball
tomorrow and

15:12.291 --> 15:16.124
it's of the utmost importance
that it's in full working order

15:21.500 --> 15:25.207
- l'll do my best, ma'am
- Right, then

15:25.958 --> 15:27.999
Goodnight, Mr Mackins

16:04.625 --> 16:06.332
Fucking thing

18:18.291 --> 18:20.082
Jesus

18:24.875 --> 18:29.707
- You're a woman  - You won't tell
on me, will you, Mr Page?

18:29.791 --> 18:33.457
- l'm on my knees
- Stop that

18:33.541 --> 18:37.790
I beg you
You won't tell on me, Mr Page?

18:37.875 --> 18:41.124
Stop a poor woman from making
a living  It will be the end of me

18:41.375 --> 18:44.624
- l don't wanna finish up
in the poorhouse  - Stop blubbering

18:44.708 --> 18:47.290
- No, no!
- Get up off the floor

18:47.375 --> 18:50.415
Get a hold of yourself! You'll wake
the entire fucking hotel!

18:50.500 --> 18:52.874
- You won't tell on me?
- Now stop with your noise!

19:00.000 --> 19:02.707
What were you doing jumping around
like that for anyway?

19:03.916 --> 19:06.457
There was a flea

19:09.166 --> 19:14.207
I'm a martyr to fleas  You must have
brought one in with you

19:14.291 --> 19:18.874
I'll be covered in blotches
in the morning

19:19.666 --> 19:24.499
All right, all right
Just get a hold of yourself

19:51.166 --> 19:53.124
So why are you dressed
like a fella?

19:53.208 --> 19:57.999
No-one would have suspected me
till the day of my death

19:58.083 --> 20:01.540
if it hadn't been for the flea
you brought with you

20:05.083 --> 20:09.207
So    Mr Nobbs

20:12.625 --> 20:14.415
what do you suggest we do now?

20:14.500 --> 20:17.457
As far as the sleeping arrangements
are concerned?

20:17.541 --> 20:19.624
Any ideas?

20:22.458 --> 20:27.249
Ah, go on, you take the bed
I'll go downstairs and find a sofa

20:27.333 --> 20:29.874
- No
- So what then?

20:29.958 --> 20:33.915
Mrs Baker will have my hide
if she finds out

20:34.000 --> 20:37.165
- You take the bed
- And where will you sleep?

20:37.250 --> 20:40.999
- Here  l don't mind
- Don't be pathetic

20:41.083 --> 20:46.665
No, please  l know her
Just promise you won't tell

20:48.416 --> 20:50.499
Jesus

20:54.166 --> 20:56.915
- All right
- You promise

20:57.000 --> 21:01.290
- you won't tell?
- Yes, l will promise anything

21:01.375 --> 21:03.957
I just need to get some sleep

21:04.708 --> 21:08.582
Here  Might as well make yourself
comfortable

21:08.666 --> 21:10.249
Have that

21:11.208 --> 21:15.415
God, I didn't ask to share
your bloody bed

21:52.500 --> 21:54.582
Bloody hell

22:59.916 --> 23:01.999
An hour late

23:02.083 --> 23:05.582
- Has 9 rung their bell yet?
- Yeah, a while ago

23:05.666 --> 23:09.040
Here
Good morning, Mr Nobbs

23:09.125 --> 23:11.082
How was your new bedfellow?

23:11.666 --> 23:13.624
I couldn't sleep, now I'm late

23:13.708 --> 23:16.665
Well l wouldn't worry my fat
about being late for one morning

23:16.750 --> 23:19.499
- Morning, Mr Nobbs
- Good morning, Mr

23:19.583 --> 23:21.874
Page  Hubert Page
Charmed to meet you

23:21.958 --> 23:24.957
- He's a shy one, our Mr Nobbs
- Oh, l know

23:25.583 --> 23:27.665
I'll bring the children's

23:43.166 --> 23:45.249
Mr Nobbs?

23:49.458 --> 23:51.915
Mrs Moore  She prefers roses

23:52.000 --> 23:55.665
- Lilies make her sneeze
- Oh, l see

23:55.750 --> 23:58.707
- Yes, well
- l heard yourself and Mr Page

23:58.791 --> 24:01.165
chattering away into the small hours

24:01.250 --> 24:03.665
He's a fine man, he is

24:05.416 --> 24:07.624
- Who?
- Mr Page

24:07.708 --> 24:12.790
- ls he married? - We didn't discuss
that sort of thing

24:13.458 --> 24:16.124
Then    what did "we" discuss?

24:22.666 --> 24:24.749
Horses

24:25.958 --> 24:28.207
Yes  Backing horses

24:28.291 --> 24:32.749
Mr Page is a great one for racing
and so on

24:35.166 --> 24:37.207
For horses

24:53.625 --> 24:56.957
A cup of tea, Mr Page?

24:58.916 --> 25:02.624
Do you know, Mr Nobbs,
I believe this house runs on tea

25:02.708 --> 25:06.540
I must have been offered 3 or 4 cups
of it already this morning

25:07.875 --> 25:09.957
Well, l wanted to

25:23.375 --> 25:27.332
- Will l take something
in to Mr Page? - Yes, good girl

25:27.416 --> 25:30.415
He wants to work through
and finish early

25:31.583 --> 25:33.832
I declare the smell of paint
from that laundry room

25:33.916 --> 25:35.540
is making me feel sick

25:35.625 --> 25:37.707
Oh, is it the morning sickness,
is it?

25:39.916 --> 25:42.957
You just think you're the funniest
thing on earth, Helen Dawes

25:43.291 --> 25:47.915
So, everyone,
this is Mr Joe Mackins

25:48.000 --> 25:50.374
He's worked all night long
and, believe it or not,

25:50.458 --> 25:52.290
he has tamed that boiler

25:52.375 --> 25:55.082
Oh, thank God for that

25:55.166 --> 25:58.582
I've been thinking that we need
a strong man about the house

25:58.666 --> 26:01.457
so l've asked Mr Mackins to stay on

26:01.541 --> 26:04.874
- Mr Nobbs    - Yes, Ma'am  - After
Mr Mackins has had something to eat,

26:04.958 --> 26:07.457
- would you show him
to the yard room? - Yes, ma'am

26:07.541 --> 26:10.665
Welcome to Morrison's, Mr Mackins

26:27.041 --> 26:30.165
Mrs Baker was talking
about a party tomorrow

26:30.250 --> 26:33.457
It's our fancy dress ball
We have it every year

26:33.541 --> 26:36.915
- We don't dress up  lt's only
for the guests  - That's a shame

26:37.000 --> 26:39.540
- Where are you from, then?
- Where are you from?

26:39.625 --> 26:41.707
- Can you not tell?
- Cork?

26:41.791 --> 26:44.665
Cork  Are you mad, are you?

26:44.750 --> 26:46.999
I am from Galway, of course

26:47.083 --> 26:49.540
I declare to my granny,
if you can't tell the difference

26:49.625 --> 26:52.207
Cork, Galway, it's all the same
to a Dublin man

26:52.291 --> 26:55.249
Oh, a Jackeen, are you?
Never would have known

26:55.333 --> 26:57.165
Born and bred in Sheriff Street,

26:57.250 --> 26:59.499
where no sheriff was ever known
to venture

27:09.791 --> 27:13.707
What delicacy have you got
for me this time, Mr Nobbs?

27:14.791 --> 27:18.832
Don't worry,
your secret's safe with me

27:18.916 --> 27:22.832
It's just    it's just I'm afraid,

27:22.958 --> 27:26.415
you see    in case Mrs Baker

28:06.208 --> 28:08.290
Mr Nobbs

28:22.958 --> 28:25.665
- You're back
- Tea-time

28:25.750 --> 28:29.082
Jesus, Mary and Joseph
Not more tea

28:34.041 --> 28:36.582
Do you want to hear my story?

28:43.750 --> 28:45.457
There's not much to tell

28:45.541 --> 28:49.790
I was married,
to a house painter as it happens

28:49.875 --> 28:53.665
A drunk and a bully
One night he came home scuttered,

28:53.750 --> 28:56.415
gave me the usual hiding

28:56.500 --> 29:00.124
only this time he rounded it off
with an almighty kick

29:02.208 --> 29:04.290
and that was the end of that

29:04.916 --> 29:06.957
What did you do?

29:15.583 --> 29:20.457
I took his things and l left
This is his work coat

29:20.541 --> 29:24.499
I kept it all these years to
remember him by, the fecking waster

29:26.250 --> 29:29.415
- So you're still married?
- l am

29:37.875 --> 29:39.790
Her name's Cathleen

29:39.875 --> 29:41.874
Girls,
it's time to start the dinner

29:41.958 --> 29:44.665
Hubert Page, have you dealt
with that damp patch yet?

29:44.750 --> 29:47.124
You're a terrible slave driver,
Mrs Donaghue

29:47.208 --> 29:49.624
And you're just a big lazy man

30:00.291 --> 30:04.124
So    you married    a woman?

30:04.250 --> 30:08.082
I met a girl as lonely as myself

30:08.916 --> 30:12.624
And we fixed up to get a place,
sharing the rent and all that

30:12.708 --> 30:16.665
She had her dressmaking,
I had me work

30:16.750 --> 30:20.957
But people began to talk
so we got married

30:22.375 --> 30:24.499
- Well
- What's your name?

30:25.666 --> 30:28.124
- Albert
- Your real name

30:30.833 --> 30:32.915
Albert

30:39.708 --> 30:43.582
Listen, Mr Page,
I hear tell you're a betting man

30:44.875 --> 30:47.082
Have you a tip for Leopardstown
tomorrow?

30:47.166 --> 30:49.707
I'm in need of a winner
I lost my shirt

30:49.791 --> 30:52.874
on "Lightning Lad" in the Gold Cup

30:52.958 --> 30:55.332
Lightning, my arse

30:56.375 --> 31:00.499
You did a grand job, Mr Page
Very salubrious

31:00.583 --> 31:01.874
Thank you, ma'am

31:01.958 --> 31:04.707
If only l could afford
to have the whole place done

31:04.791 --> 31:07.749
Could you possibly tell me,
in your expert opinion

31:07.833 --> 31:09.915
how much do you think
it'd cost?

31:10.000 --> 31:11.790
What, to paint the whole interior?

31:11.875 --> 31:15.040
Well now  Let me think

31:17.416 --> 31:19.415
Well, there's all this out here

31:20.541 --> 31:23.332
And    the coffee room

31:28.750 --> 31:30.999
- ls that a dining room?
- Yes

31:31.250 --> 31:33.457
- And how many guest floors?
- Two

31:34.625 --> 31:37.374
Well, now it's only
an estimate but

31:37.458 --> 31:40.707
I'd say it couldn't be done
for under £200

31:40.791 --> 31:45.499
200? Oh, my
Aren't I the dreamer?

31:45.583 --> 31:48.457
I can't even afford a new boiler

31:49.250 --> 31:52.165
- Goodnight, Mr Page
- Goodnight, ma'am

31:52.625 --> 31:56.874
I'll dream of more salubrious rooms

32:04.291 --> 32:07.832
- Mr Page  - God
scared the be-jaysus out of me

32:07.916 --> 32:12.290
- How did you manage it?
- What? - To marry

32:13.333 --> 32:16.999
Easy  You could do it yourself

32:17.083 --> 32:21.249
- Waiter
- Mr Moore, sir

32:21.333 --> 32:23.999
Mrs Moore and l would like a glass
of sherry before dinner

32:24.083 --> 32:27.707
- Fetch a couple of glasses up
to the room, will you? - Yes, sir

32:38.416 --> 32:42.207
- lt's been a pleasure, Mrs
Donaghue  - Go on with the fairies

32:42.375 --> 32:45.707
- l'll be counting the minutes
- Ah, go on

33:06.666 --> 33:09.415
When did he tell
his wife he was a woman?

33:13.833 --> 33:15.915
Before the wedding?

33:16.791 --> 33:18.874
Or after?

